他们是这座城市庞大而病弱的躯体上，渺小的个体，但正是因为他们的存在，才让这座骤然减速的庞大城市，能够尽量维持着运转。
They are small individuals on the city's large, sickly body, but it is because of their presence that the huge city, which has slowed down dramatically, has managed to stay afloat.
全文1402字，阅读约需3分钟▲1月28日13时7分，武汉汉口火车站，平时周边车水马龙，现在难见一辆车。
The full text of 1402 words, reading about 3 minutes January 28 13: 07, Wuhan Hankou Railway Station, usually surrounded by traffic, now difficult to see a car.
九省通衢的繁华都市，如今陷入了冰火两重天的僵持：一边是救人如救火的紧急，医院排长队，医生连轴转；一边则是空旷的马路和暗下去的万家灯火。
The thoroughfare of nine provinces, which have been thoroughfare, has become gridlocked between the exigencies of saving lives, the queues of hospitals and the rotation of doctors, and the open streets and darkening lights.
▲ 1月29日，武汉汉口沿江大道，由于公共交通停运，一名女子边骑车边拖着箱子前行。
On January 29, Wuhan Hankou along the river road, due to the suspension of public transport, a woman bicycling along the box before.
▲1月29日，武汉汉口，正在营业的烧烤店。
January 29, Wuhan Hankou, is open to the barbecue shop.
但总有一些人，出现在空空荡荡的大街上。
But there are always people out there in the empty streets.
他们是这座城市庞大而病弱的躯体上，渺小的个体，但正是因为他们的存在，才让这座骤然减速的庞大城市，能够尽量维持着运转。
They are small individuals on the city's large, sickly body, but it is because of their presence that the huge city, which has slowed down dramatically, has managed to stay afloat.
▲1月28日，蔡甸区，来自随州的包言保今年春节和妻子留守武汉，与孩子分隔两地。
January 28, Cai Dian, from Suizhou Bao Yinbao and his wife stay in Wuhan this Spring Festival, separated from their children.
空荡荡的街道上，他照常执行清扫任务。
On the empty street, he carried out his cleaning duties as usual.
▲1月31日，火神山医院建筑工地附近，警察24小时轮班，对工程车辆进行通行管理，确保道路畅通。
On January 31, fire god mountain hospital construction site, the police 24-hour shifts, engineering vehicles to carry out traffic management to ensure that the road.
中午，一名女辅警站在路边解决午饭。
At noon, a policewoman at the roadside to solve lunch.
▲1月30日，武汉协和医院西院12层隔离病房清洁区内，换好装备的北京赴鄂援助医疗队队员。
January 30, Wuhan Hsiehe Hospital West Hospital 12-storey isolation ward cleaning area, the replacement of equipment to assist members of the medical team in Beijing.
1月29日，45岁的胡先生在武汉雷神山医院工地现场又度过了一晚。
On January 29, Mr. Hu, 45, spent another night at the construction site of Wuhan Shen Shan Hospital.
他的亲属是医生，此时还战斗在抗疫一线。
His relatives were doctors, who were still fighting on the front lines of the epidemic.
而他则从医院开工那日开始，就出现在这里，见证着、参与着这所“受命于危难之中”的医院拔地而起。
And he has been here since the day the hospital was opened, witnessing and participating in the emergence of the hospital "under threat."
▲1月29日，雷神山医院建筑工地，45岁的胡先生通宵值守在现场。
On January 29, Lei Shenshan Hospital construction site, 45-year-old Mr. Hu night on duty at the scene.
据了解，胡先生的亲属也在医院坚守岗位。
It is understood that Mr. Hu's relatives are also in the hospital posts.
原本想回家的魏先生一家，最终决定留在这座奋斗了十年的城市，并且从大年初一就打开店铺售卖新鲜蔬菜，让社区多了一分平日里常常被忽略的人间烟火气。
The Wei family, who wanted to go home, decided to stay in the city for ten years and opened their shops to sell fresh vegetables on the first day of the New Year.
▲1月31日，硚口区宝丰二路，来武汉10年的魏先生一家回老家的计划搁浅后，大年初一就打开店铺在社区售卖新鲜蔬菜。
On January 31, Zhengkou District Po Fung Road, a 10-year-old Mr. Wei family back to Wuhan after the project ran aground, opened shops in the community to sell fresh vegetables on the first day of New Year.
在江岸区，40岁的货车司机肖昌文大年三十也没休息，他接到征求志愿者的通知后，就在群内组织货车司机们，自发地将物流点的物资送往各个医院。
In the Jiangxi area, 40-year-old truck driver Xiao Changwen did not rest in his late thirties, he was invited to volunteer, organized truck drivers in the group, spontaneous delivery of logistics point materials to the various hospitals.
▲1月31日，40岁的肖昌文是一名货车司机，大年三十接到征求志愿者的通知后，便组织货车司机进行调配和运输，将物资送往各个医院。
On January 31, 40-year-old Xiao Changwen is a lorry driver, after receiving a call for volunteers, the thirty-year-old truck drivers will be organized to deploy and transport goods to the various hospitals.
而另一位公交车驾驶员袁建河则在线路停运之后，为北京医疗队员提供摆渡车服务，往返驻地和武汉协和医院西院病区，从白天一直摆渡到深夜。
Another bus driver, Yuan Jianhe, provided ferry services to and from the Beijing medical team after the line was shut down. He swam late into the night between the station and the hospital's western courtyard.
▲2月1日凌晨，本该停驶的40岁公交车驾驶员袁建河为北京医疗队员提供摆渡车服务。
In the early hours of February 1, 40-year-old bus driver Yuan Jianhe, who was supposed to stop driving, provided ferry services for Beijing's medical staff.
每天往返于驻地和武汉协和医院西院病区。
Daily commute to the West Hospital of Wuhan Concorde Hospital.
他们是这个城市默默的守护者。
They are the silent guardians of the city.
像他们一样的平凡市民还有很多。
There are many ordinary citizens like them.
▲2月1日，蔡甸区，19岁的张先生来自荆州，便利店夜间鲜有人光顾，但因为这是距工地最近并还开门的便利店，他并没有松懈。
On February 1, Zhang, a 19-year-old from Jingzhou, Cai Den, seldom visited a convenience store at night, but he did not relax since it was the nearest convenience store that opened and opened the site.
▲1月31日，硚口区，宝丰街道宝地社区协管员张静正在为社区居民测量体温。
On January 31, Zhangkou District, Po Fung Street Po Toi Community Coordinator Zhang Jing is taking temperature measurements for community residents.
除为居民测量体温，社区工作人员还要为公共区域消毒。
In addition to taking temperature measurements for residents, community workers also disinfect public areas.
▲1月31日，江岸区同兴社区，为社区老人和非发热病人提供服务的出租车司机互相帮助穿上防护服。
31 January, the Jiangxi District Tongxing community, the community elderly and non-febrile taxi drivers to help each other wear protective clothing.
城市和它的人民在静默中等待疫情拐点的来临，在此之前，等待将是漫长的、惶恐的，但微小的守护汇聚在一起，就成了点燃希望的烛火，维护着这座江城的活力，等待着江河血脉重新沸腾的那一天。
Before the city and its people wait in silence for the inflection point of the epidemic, the wait will be long and fearful, but the small guards come together to light the candle of hope, to preserve the vitality of the river and to wait for the day when the rivers of blood boil again.
▲1月31日，京东物流宝丰配送站，42岁的尚黎明在管理站点的同时，兼顾搬运和运送医疗物资到医院的任务，每天工作超12小时。
On January 31, Jingdong Logistics Baofeng Distribution Station, 42-year-old Shang Dawn, while managing the site, juxtaposed the task of moving and transporting medical supplies to the hospital, working more than 12 hours a day.
